==English==
===Noun===
#a person who habitually carps, who talks too much and regularly finds fault
===Quotations===
*'''1605&ndash;1608''': By putting on the cunning of a '''carper''' &mdash; William Shakespeare, ''Timon of Athens'', 1605&ndash;1608

*'''1678''': Come, let my '''carper''' to his life now look, / And find there darker lines than in my book &mdash; John Bunyan, ''The Pilgrim's Progress'', 1678

*'''1909&ndash;1914''':He censures everything, this zealous '''carper'''. &mdash; Curtis Hidden Page's translation of ''Tartuffe or the Hypocrite'' by Jean Baptiste Poquelin Moliere, 1909&ndash;1914